- Text rendering options: context.patternQuality, context.quality, context.textDrawingMode ('path'|'glyph') with different effects for image/PDF/SVG canvases.
- Implementation notes: use registerFont for custom fonts; use createCanvas(...,'pdf') to generate PDFs; prefer createPNGStream/createPDFStream to reduce memory when encoding large outputs.

7. RFC4180 (CSV exact rules)
- Line and record rules:
  - Each record on separate line delimited by CRLF. Last record may or may not end with CRLF.
  - Optional header line allowed; header contains field names and should have the same number of fields as records.
- Field rules:
  - Fields separated by commas. Spaces are part of field content and must not be trimmed automatically.
  - Fields may be enclosed in double quotes. If not enclosed, double quotes must not appear inside the field.
  - Fields containing CRLF, commas, or double quotes must be enclosed in double quotes.
  - Double quotes inside an enclosed field must be escaped by doubling them: " becomes "".
- ABNF grammar (key rules):
  - file = [header CRLF] record *(CRLF record) [CRLF]
- MIME registration: media type text/csv; optional parameters: charset and header=(present|absent).
- Interoperability: be liberal in what you accept; handle CR, LF, CRLF; accept missing final newline.

