SUPPLEMENTARY DETAILS

- Expression evaluation performance:
  - Pre-parse expressions into AST/Expression objects (math.parse, Parser.parse from expr-eval) and evaluate with variable bindings in tight loops to avoid re-parsing overhead.
  - For high-throughput per-point evaluation (plotting thousands of points), use a compiled/evaluated function form if available.

- Image pipeline recommendations:
  - For vector->raster rendering from SVG specs use sharp or node-canvas depending on required text and font fidelity: sharp converts SVG input directly and is fast; node-canvas renders via Canvas API for programmatic drawing and PDF/SVG output.
  - When generating many thumbnails, reuse a single sharp instance pipeline connected to streams or buffers, and avoid intermediate writes to disk.
  - For text-heavy PDF generation prefer node-canvas PDF canvas with textDrawingMode 'glyph' to embed font subsets and keep PDFs selectable and smaller.

- CSV export rules for time-series data:
  - Use CRLF line endings when targeting RFC4180 compliance, include header with field names and use double-quote escaping for any field containing commas, quotes, or newlines.
  - Provide optional header parameter in HTTP responses as Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8; header=present

